CVT(TR690)-181
Forward Clutch Assembly
CONTINUOUSLY VARIABLE TRANSMISSION
37.Forward Clutch Assembly
A: REMOVAL
1) Remove the transmission from the vehicle. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-56, REMOVAL, Automatic Transmission
Assembly.>
2) Remove the extension case. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-142, REMOVAL, Extension Case.>
3) Remove the rear drive shaft. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-146, REMOVAL, Rear Drive Shaft.>
4) Remove the transfer clutch assembly. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-151, REMOVAL, Transfer Clutch.>
5) Remove the center differential carrier. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-154, REMOVAL, Center Differential Carrier.>
6) Remove the transfer reduction driven gear. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-158, REMOVAL, Transfer Reduction
Driven Gear.>
7) Remove the intermediate case. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-165, REMOVAL, Intermediate Case.>
8) Remove the thrust needle bearing.
9) Remove the forward clutch assembly.
AT-05237
AT-05238

10) Remove the washer.
B: INSTALLATION
1) Select a washer. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-199, ADJUSTMENT, Forward Clutch Assembly.>
2) Install the selected washer.
AT-05239
AT-05239

3) Install the forward clutch assembly.
4) Install the thrust needle bearing.
NOTE:
Install the thrust needle bearing in the correct direction.
5) Install the intermediate case. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-166, INSTALLATION, Intermediate Case.>
6) Install the transfer reduction driven gear assembly. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-158, INSTALLATION, Transfer
Reduction Driven Gear.>
7) Install the center differential carrier. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-155, INSTALLATION, Center Differential Car-
rier.>
8) Install the transfer clutch assembly. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-151, INSTALLATION, Transfer Clutch.>
9) Install the rear drive shaft. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-146, INSTALLATION, Rear Drive Shaft.>
10) Install the extension case. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-143, INSTALLATION, Extension Case.>
11) Install the transmission to vehicle. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-69, INSTALLATION, Automatic Transmission
Assembly.>

• Insert it all the way to the end.

11) Calculate clearance “T” from internal gear to retaining plate with the obtained value from step 5) through

Limit thickness:

22) Install the planetary carrier assembly.
E: INSPECTION
• Check the forward clutch drum, internal gear, sun gear and forward clutch piston lip for wear or damage.
• Inspect the drive plate facing for wear and damage.
• Check the driven plate for discoloration (burnt color).
• Check for worn snap ring, fatigue or damaged return spring or deformed spring retainer.
• Make sure the clearance between retaining plate and internal gear of forward clutch is within the limit. If it
exceeds the standard, replace the forward clutch assembly. <Ref. to CVT(TR690)-190, ASSEMBLY, For-
ward Clutch Assembly.>
F: ADJUSTMENT
1) Measure depth “A” from the ST upper face to the washer catch surface.
ST 398643600 GAUGE
2) Install the forward clutch assembly to intermediate case.
AT-06555
AT-07887
ST
A
15WRX_STI_US_EN.book 199 ページ ２０１５年２月１３日　金曜日　午前１１時２０分
CVT(TR690)-200
Forward Clutch Assembly

3) Setting the ST, measure height “B” from the ST upper side to the intermediate case mating surface.
ST 499575600 GAUGE
4) Obtain the thickness of washer using the following formula.
Calculation formula:
T (mm) = (A – 15) – (B – 15) – (0.35 — 0.70)
[T (in) = (A – 0.591) – (B – 0.591) – (0.014 — 0.028)]
T: Washer thickness
A: Depth from the ST upper face to the washer catch surface
B: Height from the upper surface of the ST to the mating surface of the intermediate case
15 mm (0.591 in): Thickness of ST
0.35 — 0.70 mm (0.014 — 0.028 in): Clearance
5) Select the washer to meet the value “T” obtained from step 4).
